The article highlights that inflation in the United States has reached the pre-pandemic benchmark of 2 percent over the last six months of 2023. This is seen as an important milestone for working families as it provides more breathing room. The economy has also experienced growth of over 3 percent in 2023, with unemployment remaining below 4 percent for a second year. This progress has resulted in higher wages, wealth, and employment compared to four years ago. The focus now is on lowering costs for families and opposing Republican efforts to benefit the wealthy and corporations at the expense of prescription drugs, Social Security, Medicare, and Medicaid.